<m0>Miramar Days promises 2 weeks of fun for all<ql>
<m1><ue5><m4>   TOTAL HEAD DEPTH IS .901 INCHES<m2><ql>
<ql>
<m1><styl>txt,17p8<ql>
<styl>capline,3<ql>
<styl>by <m0>By JULIE KAY<ql>
<m1><styl>crline <m0>Herald Staff Writer<ql>
<m2><ql>
<ql>
<m0>M<m2><ql>
<m0>iramar is celebrating its 41st birthday this month with Miramar Days '96 (--) two weeks of events that offer something for every age group.<ep>
   This year, for the first time, Universal Studios, producers of the children's cable television netword Nickelodeon, will hold a ``Game Lab.'' Children and adults will be chosen from the audience to participate in Nickelodeon-style games. The show will be from 1 to 3 p.m. May 18 at Miramar High School, 3601 SW 89th Ave. Tickets are $4.<ep>
   Several thousand people are expected to attend Miramar Days, which resumed in 1992 after an absence of several years.<ep>
   The festivities will begin tonight with a ``Tennis 'n Fun'' tournament at 7 p.m. at Lakeshore Park, 8501 S. Sherman Cir. The grand finale (--) a fireworks display (--) will be held at 9 p.m. at Lakeshore Park.<ep>
   Other activities include:<ep>
   (box) Basketball hotshot contest, 7 p.m. Friday at Lakeshore Park.<ep>
   (box) 10K Run, 7 p.m. Saturday at Shirley Branca Park, 6900 Miramar Pkwy.<m1><ep>
<m0>   (box) Miramar Days Pageant, featuring 140 contestants, noon Saturday at Miramar Civic Center, 6920 SW 35th St.<ep>
   (box) Calypso Festival, 6:30 p.m. May 17 at Perry Park/Wellman Field, Southwest 68th Avenue at Southwest 34th Street.<ep>
   (box) Miami Dolphins vs. City All-Stars Softball Game, 7 p.m. May 17 at Perry Park/Wellman Field. Ten Dolphins who have not yet been named will compete against city employees (no department heads will be playing). An Autograph session -- with the Dolphins not the city employees -- will follow the game.<ep>
   (box) Senior activities, including food, music, bingo and entertainment, 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. May 18 at the Miramar Senior Center, 7667 Venetian St.<ep>
   (box) Parade featuring floats, cars, horses, bagpipes and search-and-rescue dogs, 10 a.m. May 18, starting at 64th Avenue and Miramar Parkway and proceeding west on Miramar Parkway.<ep>
   (box) The ``Main Event'' at 5 p.m. May 18 at Lakeshore Park with Tux 'n Tunes D.J., game and food booths and rides. The pageant finals will follow at 5:30 p.m., and the fireworks display at 9 p.m. Bleacher seating is limited, so those attending the fireworks should bring chairs and blankets.<ep>
   Everything is free and open to the public except the Nickelodeon Game Lab.<ep>
   For more information, call 962-5501.<ql>
<m4>--9.091 inches ( 54p8 )--from start of measuring to here--<m2><ql>
